{"title": "Tulips On Fire with Mathieu Young", "slug": "playing-with-fire", "date": "2021-11-09", "author": "theline1", "excerpt": "", "categories": ["1/1", "Conceptual", "Photography", "photography"], "featuredImage": "https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/migrated/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-10-at-10.14.50-AM.png", "images": ["https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/migrated/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/3_Screen-Shot-2021-11-10-at-10.11.57-AM-801x800.png", "https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/migrated/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/2_Screen-Shot-2021-11-10-at-10.09.30-AM.png", "https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/migrated/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Screen-Shot-2021-11-10-at-10.09.30-AM-1200x621.png", "https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/migrated/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/1_Screen-Shot-2021-11-10-at-10.11.57-AM.png", "https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/migrated/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/3_Screen-Shot-2021-11-10-at-10.09.30-AM-1200x620.png", "https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/migrated/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/1_Screen-Shot-2021-11-10-at-10.09.30-AM.png", "https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/migrated/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/2_Screen-Shot-2021-11-10-at-10.11.57-AM-801x800.png", "https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/migrated/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Screen-Shot-2021-11-10-at-10.11.57-AM-801x800.png"], "content": "<p>Dangerous. Very dangerous. Guy Fawkes night celebrates a guy back in 1605 who was seriously against the establishment. While the sentiment of Guy Fawke's is lost on todays annual celebration, it still gets celebrated by letting off fireworks. Humans love fire so it is with some serendipity that I discovered Mathieu Young's work on Guw Fawke's Day 5th November 2021.</p><p><strong>Mathieu Young</strong><br />Artist based in Los Angeles playing with fire.</p><p>There are four Foundation artworks...and all are burning bright.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/migrated/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Screen-Shot-2021-11-10-at-10.09.30-AM-1200x621.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1984\" height=\"1026\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/migrated/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/1_Screen-Shot-2021-11-10-at-10.09.30-AM.png 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/migrated/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/2_Screen-Shot-2021-11-10-at-10.09.30-AM.png 1000w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/migrated/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/3_Screen-Shot-2021-11-10-at-10.09.30-AM-1200x620.png 1600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/migrated/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Screen-Shot-2021-11-10-at-10.09.30-AM-1200x621.png 1984w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><p>Fire is hypnotic to look at, most probably because it was the thing that kept humans safe from humans back in cavemen days. We continue to identify deeply with its presence. I've never seen flowers burn. I don't know if they do. </p><p>Yet I metaphorically understand that the tulip metaphor as hurled across at NFT artists is well and truly burnt out. Is that the message here? I can read the subtext.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption\"><img src=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/migrated/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Screen-Shot-2021-11-10-at-10.11.57-AM-801x800.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1988\" height=\"1986\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/migrated/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/1_Screen-Shot-2021-11-10-at-10.11.57-AM.png 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/migrated/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/2_Screen-Shot-2021-11-10-at-10.11.57-AM-801x800.png 1000w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/migrated/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/3_Screen-Shot-2021-11-10-at-10.11.57-AM-801x800.png 1600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/migrated/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Screen-Shot-2021-11-10-at-10.11.57-AM-801x800.png 1988w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"><figcaption><a href=\"https://foundation.app/@mathieuyoung/~/104273\">Burning Tulips by Mathieu Young</a> on Foundation</figcaption></figure><p>For the early mint chasers, Mathieu's <a href=\"https://foundation.app/@mathieuyoung/~/33644\">genesis work on Foundation</a> grew into mint life on May 4th 2021 and is still available. </p><hr /><p><strong><a href=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/#/portal/signup\">Subscribe to MintFace</a> and receive new artist features by email.</strong></p><p>If this article has made you curious about getting started with digital art, we also run the <a href=\"https://maven.com/cache/nft-digital-artist-economy\">Digital Artist Economy workshop</a> helping artists create their first digital art through a <a href=\"https://maven.com/cache/nft-digital-artist-economy\">three week programme.</a> Share it with an artist you'd like to see on an NFT marketplace.</p><p><strong>MintFace surfaces great artists and artworks so you don't have to. </strong></p><p><em>Enjoying MintFace? Subscribe for $9 per month.</em></p><p></p>"}